parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Front Passenger Seat Occupancy Sensor Mat Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front passenger seat occupancy sensor mat can cause the passenger airbag to not deploy in the event of a crash, potentially leading to serious injury or fatality.
symptoms: The airbag warning lamp or "Passenger Airbag OFF" lamp is activated
the passenger airbag may not deploy in a crash
and the vehicle may not detect a passenger in the front seat.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag control unit can cause the airbag to not deploy in the event of a crash, potentially leading to serious injury or fatality.
symptoms: The airbag warning light is illuminated
the airbag may not deploy in a crash
and the vehicle may experience faulty airbag deployment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay or unavailability of parts for recall repairs can leave vehicles with safety defects unrepaired, potentially leading to serious injury or fatality.
symptoms: The recall repair is delayed or unavailable
and the vehicle remains unrepaired
leaving the owner with a safety hazard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Uncontrolled acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, potentially leading to accidents and serious injury or fatality.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates out of control
and the brakes and steering fail to respond.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the vehicle to be difficult or impossible to steer, leading to accidents or loss of control, especially at high speeds or in tight spaces.
symptoms: The steering wheel feels loose or has excessive play
the vehicle is hard to steer
the steering feels manual or intermittent
the steering suddenly fails or becomes unresponsive
the power steering warning light illuminates on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electronic steering rack can cause the power steering system to fail, leading to accidents or loss of control, especially at high speeds or in tight spaces.
symptoms: The power steering warning light illuminates on the dashboard
the steering wheel feels loose or has excessive play
the vehicle is hard to steer
the steering feels manual or intermittent
the steering suddenly fails or becomes unresponsive.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering column can cause the steering system to become loose or unresponsive, leading to accidents or loss of control, especially at high speeds or in tight spaces.
symptoms: The steering wheel feels loose or has excessive play
the steering column has excessive movement or play
the vehicle is hard to steer
the steering feels manual or intermittent.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent failure of the power steering system can cause the vehicle to be difficult or impossible to steer, leading to accidents or loss of control, especially at high speeds or in tight spaces.
symptoms: The steering wheel feels loose or has excessive play
the vehicle is hard to steer
the steering feels manual or intermittent
the power steering warning light illuminates on the dashboard intermittently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The excessive brake pedal travel can cause delayed or failed braking, leading to accidents or near-misses, especially in low-speed situations such as parking or approaching stop signs.
symptoms: The brake pedal travels excessively before engaging
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal needs to be pumped to achieve improved braking
the vehicle takes longer to stop than expected.
